<Layout title="Privary Policy">
  <main>
    <h1>Our Company Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Our Company is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy explains
      how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you use Selectree, our
      website that provides information about trees and their characteristics.
    </p>

    <h2>What data do we collect?</h2>
    <p>
      We collect personal identification information such as your name, email address, and
      phone number. We also collect data about the trees you search for, the pages you
      visit, and your IP address.
    </p>

    <h2>How do we collect your data?</h2>
    <p>
      We collect your data when you visit our website, search for trees, make lists /
      saved searches, create an account, or contact us for support. We also collect data
      using cookies and similar technologies.
    </p>

    <h2>How will we use your data?</h2>
    <p>
      We will use your data to provide you with information about trees and their
      characteristics. We may also use your data to improve our website and services, as
      well as to send you marketing communications about our products and services.
    </p>

    <h2>How do we store your data?</h2>
    <p>
      We store your data in secure databases and servers located in the United States. We
      use appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against
      unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction.
    </p>

    <h2>What are your data protection rights?</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data. You can also
      object to the processing of your personal data, request a restriction on its
      processing, or request its transfer to another party. To exercise your rights,
      please contact us using the information provided below.
    </p>

    <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small files that contain information about your website preferences and
      activity. We use cookies to improve your browsing experience, personalize content,
      and analyze website traffic.
    </p>

    <h2>How do we use cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      We use cookies to remember your preferences, provide you with personalized content,
      and analyze how you use our website. We also use cookies to serve you with targeted
      advertising based on your browsing activity.
    </p>

    <h2>What types of cookies do we use?</h2>
    <p>
      We use functional cookies that enable basic website functions and cannot be switched
      off. We also use analytics cookies to track website usage and performance, as well
      as advertising cookies to serve you with targeted ads.
    </p>

    <h2>How to manage cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      You can disable cookies in your browser settings or by using an ad blocker. However,
      some parts of our website may not function properly without cookies.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy policies of other websites</h2>
    <p>
      Our website may contain links to other websites that have their own privacy
      policies. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of other websites and
      encourage you to read their privacy statements.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to our privacy policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update our privacy policy from time to time. The latest version will always
      be available on our website.
    </p>

    <h2>How to contact us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us at
      support@selectree.com.
    </p>

    <h2>How to contact the appropriate authorities</h2>
    <p>
      If you believe that we have not addressed your privacy concerns satisfactorily, you
      may contact your local data protection authority.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    margin: auto;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .text-gradient {
    background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-size: 400%;
    background-position: 0%;
  }
</style>
